# Web Interface — Accessibility & Content

Forms/navigation: `web-interface-interactions.mdc`. Primitives: `@repo/design-system` (Radix/shadcn semantics). MCP: `/docs/architecture/accessibility`.

## Next.js page context

- Each route needs a **unique, descriptive** `<title>` and visible `<h1>` — Next.js route announcer uses these for client navigations
- Use `next/image` with dimensions to prevent CLS (`react-performance.mdc`)

## Semantics (prefer native before ARIA)

- Native `<button>`, `<a>`, `<label>`, `<table>` first
- Icon-only controls → descriptive `aria-label`
- Decorative icons → `aria-hidden`
- Status not color-only — pair icon + text
- Verify names in the Accessibility Tree

## Content & states

- Design **empty, error, loading, and dense** states — no dead ends
- Skeletons mirror final layout (avoid layout shift)
- Tabular numbers: `tabular-nums` for comparisons
- Locale-aware dates, numbers, currency
- Use ellipsis character `…` (not three ASCII dots)
- `scroll-margin-top` on headings for in-page anchors; skip link to main content
- Hierarchical `h1`–`h6` — one primary heading per view

## Layout & contrast

- Respect `env(safe-area-inset-*)` on mobile
- Fix overflow — no accidental horizontal scroll
- Meet contrast on text and controls; increase on `:hover/:focus/:active`
- Test responsive: mobile, laptop, wide — use design tokens from `@repo/design-system`, not one-off hex

## Design system note

Shared primitives must expose accessible names even when visuals omit visible labels (`frontend-design-system.mdc`).

## Anti-patterns

```tsx
// ❌ Color-only error state
<span className="text-red-500">Invalid</span>

// ❌ Missing name on icon button
<button><TrashIcon /></button>

// ✅ Label + redundant cue
<button aria-label="Delete customer">
  <TrashIcon aria-hidden />
  <span className="sr-only">Delete</span>
</button>
```
